1.00	Luiz_Carlos_Barreto	Luiz Carlos Barreto	Luiz Carlos Barreto (born 20 May 1928) is a Brazilian film producer and screenwriter. He has produced 50 films since 1962. He produced the 1966 film The Priest and the Girl, which was entered into the 16th Berlin International Film Festival. He also produced the 1969 film Brazil Year 2000, which won a Silver Bear at the 19th Berlin International Film Festival.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/c6/Luiz_Carlos_Barreto.jpg/220px-Luiz_Carlos_Barreto.jpg
